The paper proposes a new training variation for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) that improves their convergence properties and performance on synthetic and image datasets. This work is primarily focused on machine learning (ML) and computer vision (CV) applications, which suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a theoretical argument for the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.GR (Graphics).
